item_text: Respect the patient's beliefs, culture, customs, and practice.

item_text: Respect patient privacy.

item_text: Follow the rules and regulations of the department and hospital.

item_text: Wear the identification badge in a visible position at all times during working hours in the hospital.

item_text: Treat professors, seniors, and people with more experience with respect and dignity.

item_text: The students' caring attention is accomplished by applying maximum efforts to respond to the patient's needs and requests as quickly as possible.
construct_definition: Clinical Performance (360-degree Evaluation Instrument)

item_text: Perform her/his duties responsibly and to the highest safety standards.

item_text: He/she is always punctual and shows up to work on time.

item_text: She/he is open to criticism.

item_text: She/he avoids all confrontation, both verbal and physical.
construct_definition: Clinical Performance (360-degree Evaluation Instrument)

item_text: The student has the ability to manage time effectively and set priorities for patient care.

item_text: The student can advocate for their patient's needs and has a reasonably high regard for each patient's wishes.
construct_definition: Clinical Performance (360-degree Evaluation Instrument)

item_text: The student is a great team member. He/she respects the position of others and works constructively and positively in the group.
construct_definition: Clinical Performance (360-degree Evaluation Instrument)

item_text: The student observes justice in dealing with different patients regardless of race, religion, opinion, gender, etc.
construct_definition: Clinical Performance (360-degree Evaluation Instrument)

item_text: In the presence of patients and companions, she/he does not criticize the colleagues decisions, and follow-up interventions are anticipated only at the patient's request or due to clinical doubt (without judging the performance of her/his colleague).
construct_definition: Clinical Performance (360-degree Evaluation Instrument)

item_text: In the event of a medical error, while accepting the responsibility, she/he takes immediate corrective measures by informing the patient's doctor/professor of the mistake so that the action can be made as soon as possible.

item_text: If she/he is not competent enough to meet the patient's needs and provide care with high quality, ask for help from the professors or peers and inform the patient about it.
construct_definition: Clinical Performance (360-degree Evaluation Instrument)

construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child look at an object when someone says look! and points to it?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child pick up and eat small pieces of food with his/her fingers?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child crawl, roll, or scoot forward on his/her own?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child transfer a small object (e.g., a small toy or stone) from one hand to the other?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child show sympathy or look concerned when others are hurt or sad?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child run more than a few steps without falling or bumping into objects?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child drink from a cup (without a lid) on his/her own without spilling?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child stack three or more small objects (e.g., blocks, cups, bottle caps) on top of each other?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child answer simple questions (e.g., do you want water?) by saying yes or no, rather than nodding?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child play with an object by making it something else? (e.g., imagining a bottle as a doll, a stone as a car, or a spoon as an airplane)
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child correctly name at least one family member other than mom and dad (e.g., name of brother, sister, aunt, uncle)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child ask for something (e.g., food, water) by name when he/she wants it?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child walk backwards?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: If the child knows an object (like a cup or an animal) and you show it to him/her, can he/she tell its name every time?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child say ten or more separate words (e.g., names like mama or objects like ball)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child imitate others behavior (e.g., washing hands or dishes)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child climb onto an object such as a chair or bench?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Is the child kind to younger children (e.g., speaks to them nicely and touches them gently)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child show curiosity to learn new things (e.g., by asking questions or exploring a new area)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child involve others in play (i.e., play interactive games with other children)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child correctly use any of the words I, you, she, or he (e.g., I go to store, or he eats rice)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child correctly ask questions using any of the words what, which, where, or who?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child count up to five objects (e.g., fingers, people)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child speak using sentences of three or more words that go together (e.g., I want water or the house is big)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: If you show the child two objects or people of different size, can he/she tell you which one is the big one and which is the small one?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child identify at least one color (e.g., red, blue, yellow)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child explain in words what common objects like a cup or a chair are used for?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: If you ask the child to give you three objects (e.g., stones, beans), does the child give you the correct amount?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child use on, in, under correctly to tell the location of the object? (e.g., the cup is on the table instead of the cup is in the table)
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child ask about familiar people other than parents when they are not there (e.g., where is the neighbor?)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child ask why questions (e.g., why are you tall?)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child remove an item of clothing (e.g., take off his/her shirt)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child tell you when he/she is tired or hungry?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child sing a short song or repeat parts of a rhyme from memory by him/herself?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child jump with both feet leaving the ground?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child become extremely withdrawn or shy in new situations?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child often kick, bite, or hit other children or adults?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child dress him/herself (e.g., put on his/her pants and shirt) without help?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child say what others like or dislike (e.g., mama doesnt like fruit, or papa likes football)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Can the child talk about things that have happened in the past using correct language (e.g., yesterday I played with my friend or last week she went to the market)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Does the child frequently act impulsively or without thinking (e.g., running into the street without looking)?
construct_definition: Child development: Caregiver Reported Early Development Index (CREDI)

item_text: Experience assessment aims the improvement of process and results

construct_definition: Questionnaire for the Self-assessment of University Service-learning Experiences (QaSLu)

item_text: Professors give feedback to students about their evolution
construct_definition: Questionnaire for the Self-assessment of University Service-learning Experiences (QaSLu)

construct_definition: Questionnaire for the Self-assessment of University Service-learning Experiences (QaSLu)

construct_definition: Questionnaire for the Self-assessment of University Service-learning Experiences (QaSLu)

construct_definition: Questionnaire for the Self-assessment of University Service-learning Experiences (QaSLu)

construct_definition: Questionnaire for the Self-assessment of University Service-learning Experiences (QaSLu)

construct_definition: Questionnaire for the Self-assessment of University Service-learning Experiences (QaSLu)
